## Terraform - # Infrastructure as Code(IaC)
Terraform is an open-source Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tool developed by HashiCorp. It allows you to define, manage, and automate cloud infrastructure using a declarative configuration language called HCL (HashiCorp Configuration Language).

## Why Use Terraform?
Infrastructure as Code (IaC): Automates infrastructure management.

Multi-Cloud Support: Works with AWS, Azure, GCP, Kubernetes, and more.

Declarative Approach: Defines the desired state of resources.

State Management: Tracks resource changes to ensure consistency.

Reusable Modules: Creates modular infrastructure components.

Version Control: Easily integrates with Git for collaboration.
